main event: Observers in Lycoming, New York reported seeing a bright object in the sky on June 3, 1966, which was later concluded to be Venus.
interesting points: The object was observed for about half an hour without discernible movement., Observers initially thought it was a UFO, but it was identified as Venus rising in the eastern sky., Venus was noted to be low on the horizon and bright during this time of year., Two reliable witnesses reported seeing a light that appeared to move slowly on June 5, 1966., Observers described the June 3 object as circular and bright, almost like car headlights.
sighted object: bright object in the sky (identified as Venus)
